---
title: Creamy Caramelized Onion Meatloaves with Sumac Roasted Green Beans & Zucchini
description: Glaze ‘em, smother ‘em, stuff ‘em—meatloaves really can do it all. These loaves mix things up with a spoonful of creamy sauce over top, made with sweet caramelized onion, cream cheese, butter, and a pinch of parsley. On the side, sumac—a tangy Middle Eastern spice—seasons carrots and zucchini with citrusy flavor (similar to lemon zest!). Serve it all together, letting the sauce pool around the veggies, for a perfectly paired plate and yet another meatloaf miracle.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6745f69b127558ca79fec015-d14d982c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6745f69b127558ca79fec015-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-caramelized-onion-meatloaves-6745f69b127558ca79fec015
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 52 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 27 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 860 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to
425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim and halve
@zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1-inch-thick half-moons.

> Trim green beans if necessary. (Save carrots for another use.)

In a #medium bowl{} (use a #large bowl{} for 4 servings), gently combine @ground beef{10%oz},
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{3/4%tsp}(we used 3⁄4 tsp; 1 1⁄4 tsp for 4),
and @pepper{}.

Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).

Place meatloaves on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. TIP: Line sheet with #foil{}
first for easier cleanup.

Toss carrots on empty side with a large
drizzle of @olive oil{}(large drizzle), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets; roast meatloaves on middle rack and carrots on top rack.

Roast on top rack until meatloaves are
cooked through and carrots are browned
and tender, ~{22-25%minutes}.

> Love extra-crispy veggies? Once meatloaves are done, remove from sheet and continue roasting
> carrots for 2-3 minutes more.

Roast meatloaves on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (skip roasting the carrots!),
then remove sheet from oven. Swap in @green beans{6%oz} for carrots; carefully toss as
instructed. Roast ~{12-15%minutes} more.

While everything roasts, halve, peel, and
thinly slice @onion{1}. Pick @parsley{1/4%oz}(leaves picked from stems; roughly chopped).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high
heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring, until softened and
lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes} (7-10 minutes
for 4 servings). Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Add a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}(large drizzle) to same #pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add onion; cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned and
softened, ~{6-9%minutes}.

> Lower heat and add a splash of water if onion begins to brown too quickly.

Add @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup} and
@sugar{3/4%tsp} (11⁄2 tsp for
4 servings) to pan with onion; cook until
thickened, ~{1-3%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) and a pinch of chopped parsley.
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Carefully toss zucchini and carrots together
with half the @sumac{1%tsp} (all for 4 servings).

Divide meatloaves and carrots and zucchini
between plates. Spoon caramelized
onion sauce over meatloaves; garnish with
remaining chopped parsley. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.